  <front>
   <head>Sonnet.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">As nearer I approach that fatal day</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Which makes all mortal cares appear so light,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Time seems on swifter wing to speed his flight,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Hope's fallacious visions fade away;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While to my fond desires, at length, I say,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Behold, how quickly melted from your sight</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The promised objects you esteemed so bright,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When love was all your song, and life looked gay!</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Now let us rest in peace! those hours are past,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And with them, all the agitating train</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">By which hope led the wandering cheated soul;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Wearied, she seeks repose, and owns at last</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How sighs, and tears, and youth, were spent in vain,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While languishing she mourned in folly's sad control.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
